---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms & Conditions | Fruit Gamer - The Ultimate Developer Merge Game" 
  description="Review the terms and conditions for playing Fruit Gamer. Standard usage policies for our online web game."
>
  <Navbar />

  <main class="w-full bg-canvas py-16 md:py-24 transition-colors duration-200">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-4 md:px-6">
      
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="mb-10 text-left border-b border-hairline pb-8">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs uppercase text-mute tracking-wider font-semibold">GET /terms-and-conditions</span>
        <h1 class="font-sans font-semibold text-3xl md:text-4xl tracking-tight text-ink mt-2 mb-4">
          Terms & Conditions
        </h1>
        <p class="text-body text-sm max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
          Last updated: June 11, 2026. Standard terms for users accessing our web applications.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Legal content -->
      <article class="prose prose-sm sm:prose max-w-none text-body font-sans leading-relaxed flex flex-col gap-6 select-text">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink tracking-tight mb-3">1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By accessing and playing the <strong>Fruit Gamer</strong> web application, you agree to comply with and be bound by these standard Terms & Conditions. If you do not agree, please do not use or access the site.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="border-t border-hairline pt-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink tracking-tight mb-3">2. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            The code physics logic, user interface components, and site layouts are the proprietary assets of Fruit Gamer. Matter.js is used under its open-source license. Fruit names, symbols, and emojis belong to their respective unicode standard descriptions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="border-t border-hairline pt-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink tracking-tight mb-3">3. Permitted Use</h2>
          <p>
            Players are granted a limited license to access and play the web game online. You may not:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>Decompile or extract the engine scripts in an attempt to replicate the core service on commercial domains.</li>
            <li>Run scripts or bots designed to automatically inject scores or bypass physics restrictions.</li>
            <li>Incorporate the game canvas into external websites using iframes without express permission.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="border-t border-hairline pt-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink tracking-tight mb-3">4. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
          <p>
            The game and its rendering loop are provided on an "as-is" and "as-available" basis. We do not warrant that gameplay will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of local cache clearings. We are not responsible for any lost high scores caused by database clearing, browser resets, or software crashes.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="border-t border-hairline pt-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink tracking-tight mb-3">5. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with standard international web compliance guidelines.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
